OL,3,CChild criminal exploitation and
OL,4,C'cuckooing' to be outlawed in new
OL,5,Clegislation
OL,7,FCuckooing is when the home of a
OL,8,Fvulnerable person is taken over
OL,9,Fwithout consent for the conduct of
OL,10,Fillegal activities like drug dealing.
OL,12,FAccording to current CPS guidance,
OL,13,Fwhen dealing with a case of suspected
OL,14,Fcuckooing, prosecutors can look to
OL,15,Foffences such as assault, harassment
OL,16,Fand modern slavery offences ` but
OL,17,Fthese may not cover all examples.
