OL,3,CChild criminal exploitation and
OL,4,C'cuckooing' to be outlawed in new
OL,5,Clegislation
OL,7,FThe legislation will also see the
OL,8,Fintroduction of CCE prevention orders,
OL,9,Fwhich will mean that courts can put
OL,10,Frestrictions on people who they
OL,11,Fbelieve pose a risk of exploiting a
OL,12,Fchild for criminal purposes.
OL,14,FBreaking these orders will also be a
OL,15,Fcriminal offence, carrying a maximum
OL,16,Fsentence of five years in prison.
OL,18,FThe Children's Commissioner has said
OL,19,Fthat the measures will provide
OL,20,F"clarity that exploited children are
OL,21,Fvictims".
