OL,5,Clegislation
OL,7,F"Introducing this new offence and new
OL,8,Fprevention orders will help create
OL,9,Fthat much needed clarity that
OL,10,Fexploited children are victims. I hope
OL,11,Fthis will enable professionals to
OL,12,Fintervene at far earlier stages of
OL,13,Fintervention, backed by plans to
OL,14,Fcreate a unique identifying number for
OL,15,Fevery child that helps services
OL,16,Fidentify those in need of support."
OL,18,FThe same Bill will also include plans
OL,19,Fto explicitly outlaw spiking, with a
OL,20,Fnew offence that will carry a prison
OL,21,Fterm of up to 10 years.
